DApps:  It has a client interface as a front-end and a back-end that includes decentraliation(blockchain and smart contracts maybe).
They depend on the functionality of a blockchain for its infrastructure and operations.
1. Provides blockchain features and services to the outside world for review, interactions and enjoyment.
2. Gives access to the blockchain for people and applications and systems, not necessarily known to each other to transact peer-to-peer.
3. It is an end-to-end application development process.


Commands to setup ethereum blockchain server locally

sudo apt-get install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:ethereum/ethereum
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install ethereum
